Programming/Coding


Install
-------

*This step is for linux mint only*

**$ sudo pluma /etc/apt/sources.list**

**Comment the last line with the character #**

*Install curl*

**$ sudo apt-get install curl**

*I don't know what is this for*

**$ command curl -sSL https://rvm.io/mpapis.asc | gpg --import -**

*Install rails*

**$ curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --rails**


Create a project
----------------

https://www.youtube.com/v/3Pbsw5jC4PI

*Initialize the rvm (if you are using it)*

**$ source ~/.rvm/bin/rvm**

*Create the app*

**$ rails new MyApp**

*Cd into it*

**$ cd MyApp**

*Initialize the server (you can use "$ rails server" instead)*

**$ rails s**

*Open the following link in your browser*

**localhost:3000**


Scaffolds
---------

https://www.youtube.com/v/Ns4yKfgJQDM

*Initialize the rvm (if you are using it)*

**$ source ~/.rvm/bin/rvm**

*Create the app*

**$ rails new MyApp**

*Cd into it*

**$ cd MyApp**

*Create the scaffold*

**$ rails generate scaffold MyScaffold my\_string:string my\_integer:integer my\_datetime:datetime my\_boolean:boolean**

*Create the database tables*

**$ rake db:migrate**

*Initialize the server (you can use "$ rails server" instead)*

**$ rails s**

*Open the following link in your browser*

**localhost:3000/my_scaffolds**


Views
-----

https://www.youtube.com/v/jdD80H-j0T0

*Initialize the rvm (if you are using it)*

**$ source ~/.rvm/bin/rvm**

*Create the app*

**$ rails new MyApp**

*Cd into it*

**$ cd MyApp**

*Create the scaffold*

**$ rails generate scaffold Message user:string message_text:text**

*Create the database tables*

**$ rake db:migrate**

*Initialize the server (you can use "$ rails server" instead)*

**$ rails s**

*Go to app/views/messages/index.html and add*

    <h1>This is a test</h1>
    <% for i in 0..10 %>
      <% if Message.find_by_user("ejemplo") %>
        <%= Message.find_by_user("ejemplo").message_text %>
      <% end %>
    <% end%>

*Open the following link in your browser*

**localhost:3000/messages**


Controllers
-----------

https://www.youtube.com/v/rvRCDLdaD_0

*Initialize the rvm (if you are using it)*

**$ source ~/.rvm/bin/rvm**

*Create the app*

**$ rails new MyApp**

*Cd into it*

**$ cd MyApp**

*Create the scaffold*

**$ rails generate scaffold Message user:string message\_text:text**

*Create the database tables*

**$ rake db:migrate**

*Initialize the server (you can use "$ rails server" instead)*

**$ rails s**

*Go to app/controllers/messages\_controllers.rb and add the line 28*

    @message.message_text="Changed the message text"

*Replace the line 32*

    format.html { redirect_to @message, notice: 'Changes were made in the controller'. }

*Open the following link in your browser*

**localhost:3000/messages**


Models
------

https://www.youtube.com/v/rvRCDLdaD_0

*Initialize the rvm (if you are using it)*

**$ source ~/.rvm/bin/rvm**

*Create the app*

**$ rails new MyApp**

*Cd into it*

**$ cd MyApp**

*Create the scaffold*

**$ rails generate scaffold Message user:string message_text:text**

*Create the database tables*

**$ rake db:migrate**

*Initialize the server (you can use "$ rails server" instead)*

**$ rails s**

*Go to app/models/message.rb and replace it*

    class Message < ActiveRecord::Base
      def myModelFunction
        return user + " says \"" + message_text + "\""
      end
    end

*Go to app/views/message/index.html.erb and add the line 19*

    <td><%= message.myModelFunction %></td>


*Open the following link in your browser*

**localhost:3000/messages**
